    narrator "{i}On her way out, Avyanna passes the intake desk. There's a line. Seven workers waiting. Eight. Nine.{/i}"
    narrator "{i}A woman near the front is arguing with the desk attendant. Her voice is sharp, desperate.{/i}"
    worker "My husband needs treatment. He can't breathe. He's been waiting since yesterday-"
    desk_attendant "{i}[[patient in the way a knife is patient]]{/i} His priority score is calculated based on productivity impact and recovery probability. Currently, there are three workers ahead of him with higher scores."
    worker "He's dying."
    desk_attendant "{i}[[beat]]{/i} His current status is \"critical-stable.\" If his status changes to \"critical-declining,\" his priority score will be recalculated. I recommend checking back in four hours."
    narrator "{i}The worker's face crumbles. She doesn't argue anymore. There's nothing to argue with.{/i}"
    narrator "{i}Avyanna keeps walking. Her footsteps echo in the corridor. Behind her, the medical bay hums with quiet, efficient neglect.{/i}"

